message.content:
cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.IT, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the language accepted by a finite automaton.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses a bijection between the representation of an integer and its decomposition as a sum of binomial coefficients, which can be seen as a data structure.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper uses logical reasoning to prove the main result.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with abstract numeration systems and their properties, which can be seen as a form of information theory.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of recognizing sets in abstract numeration systems.
